        <h2>Help</h2>
        <p>This is the help section. Here you will find answers to how to use the Museum Survey Experience administrative console. Make sure you're logged into the system before using it. Click on the appropriate question to see a detailed how-to answer, and click on the question to close it.</p>
        <h3>Surveys</h3>
        <!--Reminder when adding new sections:
            - change accordion id to whatever section it is eg surveyAccordion
            - change href to be appropriate question #
        -->
        <div class="accordion" id="surveyAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-group">
                <div class="accordion-heading">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#surveyAccordion" href="#sq1">
                        How do I create a survey?
                    </a>
                </div>
                <div id="sq1" class="accordion-body collapse">
                    <div class="accordion-inner">
                        <ol>
                            <li class="help-li">Navigate to the Surveys screen and click on the blue button labeled "Create New Survey"<br /><img class="help-img" src="~/Content/images/faq/create1.png" /></li>
                            <li class="help-li">Enter a Survey Name, a Survey Description, and select a theme from the drop down menu. Survey Names and Description will appear on the welcome screen to the surveys, see the image below to see how they're used. Note that Survey Name will be put between "Welcome to the" and "Survey!", so keep that in mind when making a survey name.<br /><img src="~/Content/images/faq/create2.png" class="help-img" /></li>
                            <li class="help-li">Click the button labeled "+Add Question" to add a question to the survey. Surveys require at least one question.</li>
                            <li class="help-li">In the box marked "Text", enter a question.</li>
                            <li class="help-li">
                                Select a question type from the dropdown marked "Type". The different question types are as follows:
                                <br />&bull; MultipleChoiceChooseMany - A multiple choice question that allows the user to select as many options as they want. An option is available to limit the number of options selected.
                                <br />&bull; MultipleChoiceChooseOne - A multiple choice question that only allows one answer from the user.
                                <br />&bull; ShortAnswer - A free-form text box for users to enter text into.
                                <br />&bull; Slider - A slider that allows the user to select an option between a range of values. Requires three choices.
                                <br />&bull; ExhibitsChooseMany - A special question type that allows users to select their favorite exhibits.
                                <br />&bull; Spinner - A number input question that gives the user up and down buttons to select their response.
                            </li>
                            <li class="help-li">For questions that require at least one choice (MultipleChoiceChooseMany, MultipleChoiceChooseOne, Slider), click the button marked "+Add Choice" and fill out the required information. <br /><img src="~/Content/images/faq/create4.png" class="help-img"><br />"The "Image" option allows you to add an image that appears next to the choice text in the survey.<br /><img src="~/Content/images/faq/create3.png" class="help-img" /></li>
                            <li class="help-li">To delete a choice, click the red X to the right of the choice.</li>
                            <li class="help-li">To delete a question, click the red X at the top right corner of the question box.</li>
                            <li class="help-li">To change the order of the questions, click the title of the question you want to move and drag it to the location you want.<br /><img src="~/Content/images/faq/create5.png" class="help-img" /></li>
                            <li class="help-li">Save the survey by clicking the green button labeled "Save".</li>
                            <li class="help-li">You have now completed a survey!</li>
                        </ol>
                        <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#surveyAccordion" href="#sq1">
                            Close Question
                        </a> | <a href="#">Back to top</a>
                        <hr />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-group">
                <div class="accordion-heading">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#surveyAccordion" href="#sq2">
